<section class="comments">
<h4><br>
<a id="comments"></a>Please  read  this before posting a comment or question</h4>
<p><img src="http://amazingribs.com/images/elements/grouchy.jpg" alt="grouchy?" width="200" height="220" class="fltrght" />1) Please use the <a href="http://amazingribs.com/table_of_contents.html">table of contents</a> or the <a href="#search">search box</a> at the top of every page before you ask for help, then please post your question on the appropriate page.</p>
<p> 2) Please tell us <em>everything</em> we need to know to answer your question such as the type of cooker and  thermometer you are using.  Dial thermometers are often off by as much as 50°F so if you are not using a good digital thermometer <em> we probably can't help you</em>.  Please read <a href="http://amazingribs.com/BBQ_buyers_guide/thermometer_buying_guide.html">this article about thermometers</a>.</p>
<p> 3) If you post a photo,  wait a minute for a thumbnail to appear. It will happen even if you don't see it happen.</p>
<p> 4) 
Click here to learn <a href="http://amazingribs.com/terms_of_service.html">more about our comment system and our privacy promise</a>. Remember, your login info for comments  is probably different from your <a href="http://amazingribs.com/pitmaster_club/index.html">Pitmaster Club</a> login info if you are a member.</p>
